CB Kyu Blu-Kelly Stanford 74
info: 0 INT 3 PBU 32 tackles 57.3 TACK 64.9 COV. 6’0 193 with 31 ¾ arms.
pros: Went to Stanford so a smart kid. Did a very good job vs Drake London in 2021. Smooth player that can accelerate and change direction well. Used to press coverage where he gets hands on. His dad played in the NFL as a DB. Started for 4 straight seasons.
cons: Not a strong corner, will get blocked easy and have a tough time making tackles. Long speed isn’t great, tough time making up ground. Doesn’t have the dog in him where he needs to make plays.
